<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-03T13:20:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="75" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/75</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Antwerp</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DHW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Diederich</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Antwerp</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-08-03T13:20:00-05:00" notBefore="1914-08-03T00:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 3,
                                1914, 1:20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Germany asked permission enter Belgian territory which was refused,
                            whereupon martial law declared. Antwerp City in state siege. Situation
                            very grave. Demands immediate relief, protection, provisions,
                            transportation. Thousands of Americans in Antwerp and Belgium.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Consul General</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>